HP has unveiled a new Windows Mixed Reality headset, which it calls the Professional Edition. The company also showed off its VR Launch Kit for Unreal Engine, designed to accelerate VR development and optimise VR deployment for high-fidelity use-cases. The Professional Edition headset features a 1,440 x 1,440 resolution per eye and up to a 90Hz refresh rate. “Users will enjoy the six degrees of freedom, no tracking boundaries, and the included wireless motion controllers,” said HP. On the software side, HP’s VR Launch Kit for Unreal Engine is a suite of tools developed for businesses by HP and Epic Games. The HP Windows Mixed Reality Headset Professional Edition is scheduled for sale in March for $449.